<anchor xml:id="_group___r_c_c___h_s_i___configuration_1ga36991d340af7ad14b79f204c748b0e3e"/>    <section>
    <title>__HAL_RCC_HSI_CALIBRATIONVALUE_ADJUST</title>
<indexterm><primary>__HAL_RCC_HSI_CALIBRATIONVALUE_ADJUST</primary><secondary>HSI Configuration</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>HSI Configuration</primary><secondary>__HAL_RCC_HSI_CALIBRATIONVALUE_ADJUST</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>#define __HAL_RCC_HSI_CALIBRATIONVALUE_ADJUST( _HSICALIBRATIONVALUE_)             (MODIFY_REG(RCC-&gt;CR, <link linkend="_group___peripheral___registers___bits___definition_1ga5cb4397b2095c31660a01b748386aa70">RCC_CR_HSITRIM</link>, (uint32_t)(_HSICALIBRATIONVALUE_) &lt;&lt; RCC_CR_HSITRIM_Pos))</computeroutput></para><para>

<para>Macro to adjust the Internal High Speed oscillator (HSI) calibration value. </para>
</para>

<para><note><title>Note</title>

<para>The calibration is used to compensate for the variations in voltage and temperature that influence the frequency of the internal HSI RC. </para>
</note>

                <formalpara>
                    <title>
Parameters                    </title>
                    <para>
